# LICENSE

## Documentation and media

The project documentation, photos, videos, and audio published as part of the documentation are shared under the **Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International** license (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0).

You are free to:
- Share — copy and redistribute the material in any medium or format
- Adapt — remix, transform, and build upon the material

Under the following terms:
- **Attribution** — You must give appropriate credit, provide a link to the license, and indicate if changes were made.
- **NonCommercial** — You may not use the material for commercial purposes.
- **ShareAlike** — If you remix, transform, or build upon the material, you must distribute your contributions under the same license.

Full license text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/

## Hardware design files

Hardware design files are released under the **CERN Open Hardware Licence Version 2 - Strongly Reciprocal** (CERN-OHL-S v2), with an additional non-commercial restriction.

This means:
- **Attribution** — You must retain all copyright notices and give appropriate credit.
- **ShareAlike** — Any modifications or derivative hardware must be released under the same license.
- **NonCommercial** — You may not use these hardware designs for commercial purposes without prior written permission from the copyright holder.

Full CERN-OHL-S v2 license text: https://ohwr.org/cern_ohl_s_v2.txt

## Source code

Source code is released under the **PolyForm Noncommercial License 1.0.0**.

You are free to:
- Use the software for non-commercial purposes
- Modify and create derivative works
- Share the software with others

Under the following terms:
- **Attribution** — You must retain all copyright notices and give appropriate credit.
- **NonCommercial** — You may not use the software for commercial purposes without prior written permission from the copyright holder.

Full license text: https://polyformproject.org/licenses/noncommercial/1.0.0/

